Sec. 20001: Provides $230.48 million for Marine Corps Barracks 2030 modernization, $1 billion for unaccompanied housing across the Army, Navy, Air Force, and Space Force, and $2 billion for the Defense Health Program, all appropriated from Treasury funds outside the regular budget for FY2025 and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20002: Allocates $250 million for expanded defense manufacturing training, $450 million for U.S. additive manufacturing for shipbuilding, $4.6 billion for a second Virginia-class submarine in FY2026, $5.4 billion for two additional DDG destroyers, and $1.8 billion for Landing Ship Medium procurement, all funded from Treasury appropriations outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20003: Appropriates $250 million for directed energy missile defense development, $2 billion for air-moving target indicator satellites, $5.6 billion for space-based intercept capabilities, $7.2 billion for military space-based sensors, and $2.55 billion for missile defense integration, all from Treasury funds outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20004: Provides $400 million for long-range anti-ship missile development, $630 million for long-range Navy air defense missiles, $688 million for multi-service cruise missiles, $1 billion for automated munitions production factories, and $2 billion for critical mineral stockpile improvements, all appropriated from Treasury funds outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20005: Allocates $1.4 billion for small unmanned aerial system industrial base expansion, $600 million for Strategic Capabilities Office programs, $1 billion for low-cost cruise missile development, and $1 billion for Department of Defense credit program capital assistance, all from Treasury appropriations outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20006: Provides $150 million for business systems replacement to accelerate DoD financial audits, $200 million for AI-driven audit automation, and $20 million for DARPA cybersecurity programs, all appropriated from Treasury funds outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20007: Appropriates $3.15 billion to increase F-15EX production, $400 million to accelerate F-47 aircraft production, $750 million to accelerate FA/XX aircraft development, and $600 million for Air Force long-range strike aircraft, all from Treasury funds outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20008: Provides $2.5 billion for Sentinel ICBM risk reduction, $4.5 billion for B-21 bomber production expansion, $2 billion for nuclear-armed sea-launched cruise missile development, and $750 million each for primary and secondary nuclear capability modernization, all appropriated from Treasury funds outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20009: Allocates $365 million for Army exercises in the Western Pacific, $1.1 billion for infrastructure development in Indo-Pacific Command areas of operations, $1 billion for offensive cyber operations, and $3.65 billion for military satellite development and integration, all from Treasury appropriations outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20010: Provides $2.5 billion for Navy depot modernization, $1.64 billion for Special Operations Command equipment and readiness, $2.1 billion for Air Force facilities sustainment, and $320 million for Joint Special Operations Command, all appropriated from Treasury funds outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20011: Appropriates $1 billion for military support of border operations, counter-narcotics missions, and migrant detention at DoD installations, funded from Treasury outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20012: Provides $10 million for the DoD Inspector General to monitor programs with technological dependencies, data management issues, and supply chain vulnerabilities, appropriated from Treasury outside the regular budget and available until September 30, 2029.

Sec. 20013: Authorizes funds for military construction projects across all military departments, with each department required to submit a detailed spending plan within 30 days of enactment to the Armed Services Committees of both houses of Congress. [end of text]


